00:26:21.045 --> 00:26:23.170 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Isn't that what
happened to Bernie Madoff?

00:26:23.170 --> 00:26:24.460 align:middle line:90%
That's how he collapsed?

00:26:24.460 --> 00:26:25.260 align:middle line:90%
>>FITTS: Right.

00:26:25.260 --> 00:26:26.060 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Same way.

00:26:26.060 --> 00:26:28.260 align:middle line:84%
>>FITTS: Well, but here's
what's interesting.

00:26:28.260 --> 00:26:30.750 align:middle line:84%
I interviewed one
of the attorneys who

00:26:30.750 --> 00:26:32.850 align:middle line:84%
was an investor in Madoff
and then represented

00:26:32.850 --> 00:26:34.810 align:middle line:90%
a lot of the Madoff victims.

00:26:34.810 --> 00:26:37.020 align:middle line:90%
And she sued the bank.

00:26:37.020 --> 00:26:41.450 align:middle line:84%
So I was interviewing her
on the "Solari Report."

00:26:41.450 --> 00:26:43.290 align:middle line:84%
This was one of those
shocking moments

00:26:43.290 --> 00:26:46.980 align:middle line:84%
that I know it happens to
you at "Coast to Coast".

00:26:46.980 --> 00:26:49.830 align:middle line:84%
So I'm in the middle, and
she had sued the bank.

00:26:49.830 --> 00:26:55.350 align:middle line:84%
And under bank secrecy laws
and Know Your Customer,

00:26:55.350 --> 00:26:57.840 align:middle line:84%
banks aren't supposed to be
doing the kind of shenanigans

00:26:57.840 --> 00:26:59.007 align:middle line:90%
they were doing with Madoff.

00:26:59.007 --> 00:27:05.550 align:middle line:84%
So Madoff had one bank account
from the mid-'90s on, and all

00:27:05.550 --> 00:27:07.140 align:middle line:90%
the money went in there.

00:27:07.140 --> 00:27:10.170 align:middle line:84%
And her name was Helen
Shayman-- amazing woman.

00:27:10.170 --> 00:27:13.688 align:middle line:84%
And so all the money went in,
and then all the money went out

00:27:13.688 --> 00:27:14.730 align:middle line:90%
of that one bank account.

00:27:14.730 --> 00:27:17.460 align:middle line:84%
So was I was interviewing
her, and I said,

00:27:17.460 --> 00:27:20.130 align:middle line:84%
Helen, who was the
securities custodian?

00:27:20.130 --> 00:27:22.380 align:middle line:84%
She said, there was
none, because there

00:27:22.380 --> 00:27:24.060 align:middle line:90%
were no securities.

00:27:24.060 --> 00:27:27.180 align:middle line:84%
So here you have a $60 billion
money management business,

00:27:27.180 --> 00:27:29.310 align:middle line:84%
and there's no
securities, and there's

00:27:29.310 --> 00:27:30.943 align:middle line:90%
no securities custodian.

00:27:30.943 --> 00:27:32.610 align:middle line:84%
And the bank knew,
because all the money

00:27:32.610 --> 00:27:33.527 align:middle line:90%
went in, and went out.

00:27:33.527 --> 00:27:35.260 align:middle line:84%
And the bank knew
over all those years.

00:27:35.260 --> 00:27:36.990 align:middle line:90%
So it was over 10 years.

00:27:36.990 --> 00:27:38.610 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Did the
bank use the money?

00:27:38.610 --> 00:27:41.040 align:middle line:84%
>>FITTS: Yeah, there were
huge balances sitting, not

00:27:41.040 --> 00:27:42.610 align:middle line:90%
earning interest.

00:27:42.610 --> 00:27:43.410 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Wow.

00:27:43.410 --> 00:27:45.035 align:middle line:84%
>>FITTS: So something
else is going on.

00:27:45.035 --> 00:27:48.583 align:middle line:84%
And to this day, I would love
to know what was going on,

00:27:48.583 --> 00:27:49.500 align:middle line:90%
but I don't know what.

00:27:49.500 --> 00:27:52.200 align:middle line:84%
It was clearly an
officially-sanctioned

00:27:52.200 --> 00:27:54.720 align:middle line:90%
operation, in my opinion.

00:27:54.720 --> 00:27:58.110 align:middle line:84%
I was on the board of
the First American Bank.

00:27:58.110 --> 00:28:02.320 align:middle line:84%
Do you remember the
Clark Clifford bank in--

00:28:02.320 --> 00:28:03.120 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:28:03.120 --> 00:28:03.920 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Oh, yeah.

00:28:03.920 --> 00:28:06.900 align:middle line:84%
>>FITTS: So Harry Albright,
who'd been a client of mine

00:28:06.900 --> 00:28:08.730 align:middle line:90%
and was a wonderful man--

00:28:08.730 --> 00:28:11.580 align:middle line:84%
Morgenthau had made him
the trustee of the bank.

00:28:11.580 --> 00:28:14.550 align:middle line:84%
So this is all part
of the BCCI mess.

00:28:14.550 --> 00:28:15.480 align:middle line:90%
So Harry calls me.

00:28:15.480 --> 00:28:17.940 align:middle line:84%
He says, I need a
ringer on the board.

00:28:17.940 --> 00:28:21.230 align:middle line:84%
And I said, if you want
me, Harry, I'm there.

00:28:21.230 --> 00:28:22.030 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: I'm there.

00:28:22.030 --> 00:28:26.010 align:middle line:84%
>>FITTS: So had this huge glass
house in McLean, Virginia.

00:28:26.010 --> 00:28:31.830 align:middle line:84%
And Harry has the law firm
bring the documents out.

00:28:31.830 --> 00:28:33.060 align:middle line:90%
I had a very steep driveway.

00:28:33.060 --> 00:28:37.320 align:middle line:84%
This huge Brink's truck spends
an hour getting up my driveway.

00:28:37.320 --> 00:28:40.128 align:middle line:84%
And then, they back out
box after box of books.

00:28:40.128 --> 00:28:41.670 align:middle line:84%
And I had this living
room that was--

00:28:41.670 --> 00:28:43.620 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And you're supposed
to look at all these?

00:28:43.620 --> 00:28:45.120 align:middle line:84%
>>FITTS: Well, I'm
a speed reader.

00:28:45.120 --> 00:28:48.420 align:middle line:10%
So it was on a Thursday,
and I spent four days just

00:28:48.420 --> 00:28:49.910 align:middle line:10%
speed reading all
those documents.

00:28:49.910 --> 00:28:50.760 align:middle line:10%
>>NOORY: Jeez.

00:28:50.760 --> 00:28:52.570 align:middle line:10%
>>FITTS: And it changed my life.

00:28:52.570 --> 00:28:55.020 align:middle line:84%
So I'm in this huge
glass living room.

00:28:55.020 --> 00:28:57.690 align:middle line:84%
I'm overlooking
the Potomac River.

00:28:57.690 --> 00:29:00.330 align:middle line:84%
And I got the boxes spread out
all over in this living room.

00:29:00.330 --> 00:29:02.470 align:middle line:84%
And I read thousands and
thousands and thousands

00:29:02.470 --> 00:29:03.270 align:middle line:90%
of pages.

00:29:03.270 --> 00:29:04.770 align:middle line:84%
And when it was
over what I realized

00:29:04.770 --> 00:29:09.270 align:middle line:84%
is, whatever they were doing
had approval from the Fed.

00:29:09.270 --> 00:29:11.010 align:middle line:84%
It had approval from
the New York Fed.

00:29:11.010 --> 00:29:13.578 align:middle line:84%
It had approval
from the Treasury.

00:29:13.578 --> 00:29:15.870 align:middle line:84%
In other words, you're talking
about something that had

00:29:15.870 --> 00:29:17.390 align:middle line:90%
to be officially sanctioned.

00:29:17.390 --> 00:29:18.390 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: That's amazing.

00:29:18.390 --> 00:29:19.980 align:middle line:90%
It's frightening.

00:29:19.980 --> 00:29:22.020 align:middle line:84%
>>FITTS: It was frightening,
it was frightening.

00:29:22.020 --> 00:29:24.250 align:middle line:90%
And part of it was the fight.

00:29:24.250 --> 00:29:26.760 align:middle line:84%
And the reason Harry
wanted some ringers--

00:29:26.760 --> 00:29:29.400 align:middle line:84%
the Department of Justice was
trying to seize the proceeds,

00:29:29.400 --> 00:29:32.460 align:middle line:84%
and Harry wanted the proceeds
to go back to the depositors.

00:29:32.460 --> 00:29:33.750 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Who won?

00:29:33.750 --> 00:29:35.070 align:middle line:90%
>>FITTS: I think Harry won--

00:29:35.070 --> 00:29:35.730 align:middle line:90%
yeah, if I remember.

00:29:35.730 --> 00:29:37.105 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: In your
particular case,

00:29:37.105 --> 00:29:39.810 align:middle line:84%
you're one of the few people
talking about this publicly.

00:29:39.810 --> 00:29:42.090 align:middle line:84%
Are you looking
over your shoulder?

00:29:42.090 --> 00:29:43.548 align:middle line:84%
Because you should
be, Catherine.

00:29:43.548 --> 00:29:45.090 align:middle line:84%
>>FITTS: Well, during
the litigation,

00:29:45.090 --> 00:29:46.825 align:middle line:90%
I had to look over my shoulder.

00:29:46.825 --> 00:29:49.450 align:middle line:84%
It was very dangerous, and it's
quite a miracle that I'm alive.

00:29:49.450 --> 00:29:50.250 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: It is.

00:29:50.250 --> 00:29:51.210 align:middle line:90%
It's a lot of money.

00:29:51.210 --> 00:29:53.700 align:middle line:84%
>>FITTS: Well, but
here's the thing--

00:29:53.700 --> 00:29:56.235 align:middle line:84%
we all come into this
life with a purpose.

00:29:56.235 --> 00:29:59.150 align:middle line:90%


00:29:59.150 --> 00:30:04.170 align:middle line:84%
I would love to see
America turn around.

00:30:04.170 --> 00:30:05.690 align:middle line:84%
And one of the
reasons I ended up

00:30:05.690 --> 00:30:07.340 align:middle line:90%
in such an enemy of the state--

00:30:07.340 --> 00:30:09.422 align:middle line:84%
litigation with the
federal government--

00:30:09.422 --> 00:30:10.880 align:middle line:84%
is, when I saw what
they were doing

00:30:10.880 --> 00:30:13.460 align:middle line:84%
in the '90s was
stealing the money,

00:30:13.460 --> 00:30:17.210 align:middle line:84%
the thing that bothered
me the most was the HUD

00:30:17.210 --> 00:30:18.740 align:middle line:84%
and the Department
of Justice were

00:30:18.740 --> 00:30:21.170 align:middle line:84%
dropping SWAT teams into
black neighborhoods,

00:30:21.170 --> 00:30:24.590 align:middle line:84%
rounding up innocent kids,
stuffing them in prison.

00:30:24.590 --> 00:30:27.073 align:middle line:84%
My old firm was making
money on the prison stocks.

00:30:27.073 --> 00:30:28.490 align:middle line:84%
If you read the
Dillon Reed story,

00:30:28.490 --> 00:30:29.780 align:middle line:90%
it describes all of that.

00:30:29.780 --> 00:30:32.450 align:middle line:84%
But basically, if you look
at what they were doing--

00:30:32.450 --> 00:30:36.560 align:middle line:84%
both with globalization and the
re-engineering domestically--

00:30:36.560 --> 00:30:38.990 align:middle line:84%
the world I was
part of had a plan,

00:30:38.990 --> 00:30:42.240 align:middle line:84%
and I thought their
plan was going to fail.

00:30:42.240 --> 00:30:45.080 align:middle line:84%
And so when I left the
Bush administration,

00:30:45.080 --> 00:30:47.218 align:middle line:84%
I had created Hamilton
Securities to come up

00:30:47.218 --> 00:30:48.260 align:middle line:90%
with an alternative plan.

00:30:48.260 --> 00:30:49.060 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Right.

00:30:49.060 --> 00:30:51.233 align:middle line:84%
>>FITTS: I said,
look, we can't--

00:30:51.233 --> 00:30:53.150 align:middle line:84%
people want to be part
of something excellent.

00:30:53.150 --> 00:30:56.750 align:middle line:84%
They don't want to be
part of organized crime.

00:30:56.750 --> 00:30:58.670 align:middle line:84%
And I just thought,
at some point,

00:30:58.670 --> 00:31:00.530 align:middle line:84%
you've got to decide
between, are we

00:31:00.530 --> 00:31:04.190 align:middle line:84%
going to run this clean or are
we going to run this dirty?

00:31:04.190 --> 00:31:06.980 align:middle line:90%
And if you have to choose--

00:31:06.980 --> 00:31:09.740 align:middle line:84%
I've always said, civilization
is the biggest capital gains

00:31:09.740 --> 00:31:12.140 align:middle line:84%
opportunity on the
planet, [LAUGHS]

00:31:12.140 --> 00:31:14.030 align:middle line:84%
because I really do
believe in markets.

00:31:14.030 --> 00:31:17.500 align:middle line:84%
I don't think technocracy
is going to work.

00:31:17.500 --> 00:31:20.270 align:middle line:84%
But their plan was
basically technocracy.

00:31:20.270 --> 00:31:23.418 align:middle line:84%
And if you looked at it,
as a financial matter,

00:31:23.418 --> 00:31:24.710 align:middle line:90%
I thought it was going to lose.

00:31:24.710 --> 00:31:27.350 align:middle line:84%
So I said, I don't want
to be a part of it.

00:31:27.350 --> 00:31:28.150 align:middle line:90%
And it's funny--

00:31:28.150 --> 00:31:29.690 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Well, that was
smart on your part--

00:31:29.690 --> 00:31:30.890 align:middle line:90%
>>FITTS: But no, I didn't--

00:31:30.890 --> 00:31:32.730 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: --but dangerous.

00:31:32.730 --> 00:31:34.580 align:middle line:84%
>>FITTS: Yeah, but
here's the thing--

00:31:34.580 --> 00:31:35.870 align:middle line:90%
I didn't come here to be safe.

00:31:35.870 --> 00:31:38.930 align:middle line:84%
I came here to live a
free and inspired life.

00:31:38.930 --> 00:31:39.860 align:middle line:90%
And if you go back--

00:31:39.860 --> 00:31:42.500 align:middle line:84%
I'm a Christian--
and particularly,

00:31:42.500 --> 00:31:46.400 align:middle line:84%
if you study Jesus
and what he taught,

00:31:46.400 --> 00:31:50.720 align:middle line:84%
if you read his letter to
the Galatians, he said,

00:31:50.720 --> 00:31:52.970 align:middle line:90%
reject the yoke of bondage.

00:31:52.970 --> 00:31:55.370 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: You just wrote a book
called, "Dillon Read & the

00:31:55.370 --> 00:31:57.320 align:middle line:90%
Aristocracy of Stock Prophets."

00:31:57.320 --> 00:32:00.420 align:middle line:84%
Let's take a look
at this in depth.

00:32:00.420 --> 00:32:02.910 align:middle line:10%
>>FITTS: There's an old
New Jersey street saying--

00:32:02.910 --> 00:32:05.860 align:middle line:10%
make a law, make a business.

00:32:05.860 --> 00:32:08.220 align:middle line:10%
And that's what
this story is about.

00:32:08.220 --> 00:32:11.880 align:middle line:84%
It starts with the
popsicle index.

00:32:11.880 --> 00:32:14.090 align:middle line:84%
The popsicle index
is the percentage

00:32:14.090 --> 00:32:16.660 align:middle line:84%
of people in a
community who believe

00:32:16.660 --> 00:32:19.310 align:middle line:84%
a child can leave their
home, go to the nearest place

00:32:19.310 --> 00:32:23.620 align:middle line:84%
to buy a popsicle, and
come home alone safely.

00:32:23.620 --> 00:32:27.430 align:middle line:10%
When I was a little girl, the
popsicle index was very high.

00:32:27.430 --> 00:32:31.730 align:middle line:90%
Today, it is much lower.

00:32:31.730 --> 00:32:37.220 align:middle line:10%
During this time, the Dow
Jones index rose by over 6000%.

00:32:37.220 --> 00:32:41.390 align:middle line:10%
Why are the popsicle index and
the Dow Jones index at odds?

00:32:41.390 --> 00:32:42.500 align:middle line:10%
Cui Bono?

00:32:42.500 --> 00:32:44.090 align:middle line:90%
Who benefits?

00:32:44.090 --> 00:32:47.350 align:middle line:84%
Who makes money in the stock
market from a falling popsicle

00:32:47.350 --> 00:32:49.300 align:middle line:90%
index?

00:32:49.300 --> 00:32:53.210 align:middle line:84%
This is the story of my search
for answers to these questions

00:32:53.210 --> 00:32:55.270 align:middle line:84%
and of my hope for a
world that preserves

00:32:55.270 --> 00:32:58.930 align:middle line:84%
the promise of a rising
popsicle index for our children

00:32:58.930 --> 00:33:00.526 align:middle line:90%
and generations yet unborn.

00:33:00.526 --> 00:33:03.442 align:middle line:10%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:33:03.442 --> 00:33:06.360 align:middle line:90%


00:33:06.360 --> 00:33:08.240 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: The
popsicle index, huh?

00:33:08.240 --> 00:33:10.040 align:middle line:84%
>>FITTS: So I discovered
this when I was

00:33:10.040 --> 00:33:11.390 align:middle line:90%
Assistant Secretary of Housing.

00:33:11.390 --> 00:33:14.210 align:middle line:84%
The first month, I
kept being lobbied

00:33:14.210 --> 00:33:18.560 align:middle line:84%
by all the home construction
industry and the mortgage

00:33:18.560 --> 00:33:20.005 align:middle line:90%
finance industry.

00:33:20.005 --> 00:33:21.380 align:middle line:84%
And what I realized
is, everybody

00:33:21.380 --> 00:33:23.630 align:middle line:84%
was lobbying me to do whatever
made their stock go up.

00:33:23.630 --> 00:33:26.088 align:middle line:84%
And nobody cared about whether
neighborhoods worked or not,

00:33:26.088 --> 00:33:28.080 align:middle line:84%
or whether families
were successful.

00:33:28.080 --> 00:33:32.010 align:middle line:90%
And I thought, this is strange.

00:33:32.010 --> 00:33:33.930 align:middle line:84%
And what I realized
is, there was

00:33:33.930 --> 00:33:36.690 align:middle line:84%
no place-based optimization,
because government money

00:33:36.690 --> 00:33:38.340 align:middle line:90%
was running places.

00:33:38.340 --> 00:33:40.350 align:middle line:84%
And government money
was running places

00:33:40.350 --> 00:33:43.520 align:middle line:84%
in a way that had what I call a
negative return on investment.

00:33:43.520 --> 00:33:46.380 align:middle line:84%
It was using the government as a
device to sort of launder money

00:33:46.380 --> 00:33:48.895 align:middle line:84%
into people who have made
money in the stock market.

00:33:48.895 --> 00:33:50.130 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Let them make more.

00:33:50.130 --> 00:33:50.930 align:middle line:90%
>>FITTS: Right.

00:33:50.930 --> 00:33:54.630 align:middle line:84%
Well, to me, I love making money
in the stock market, George.

00:33:54.630 --> 00:33:55.980 align:middle line:90%
I'm an investment banker.

00:33:55.980 --> 00:33:56.780 align:middle line:90%
So to me, that's--

00:33:56.780 --> 00:33:57.480 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Sure,
that's what you do.

00:33:57.480 --> 00:33:59.490 align:middle line:90%
>>FITTS: Yeah, yeah, it's great.

00:33:59.490 --> 00:34:02.160 align:middle line:84%
But what I realized is we
have a win-lose relationship

00:34:02.160 --> 00:34:06.870 align:middle line:84%
between the Dow Jones
index and communities.

00:34:06.870 --> 00:34:09.969 align:middle line:84%
So all my work at Hamilton
was, how do we change that?

00:34:09.969 --> 00:34:12.690 align:middle line:84%
It's part of making
the red button green.

00:34:12.690 --> 00:34:15.150 align:middle line:84%
How do we make
money turning this

00:34:15.150 --> 00:34:16.469 align:middle line:90%
into a win-win relationship?

00:34:16.469 --> 00:34:18.810 align:middle line:84%
Because if we're going to
make America great again,

00:34:18.810 --> 00:34:22.080 align:middle line:84%
we're either going to gentrify
Americans out of existence

00:34:22.080 --> 00:34:25.770 align:middle line:84%
and destroy them, or we're going
to change that relationship

00:34:25.770 --> 00:34:27.330 align:middle line:90%
to win-win, lose-lose.

00:34:27.330 --> 00:34:30.330 align:middle line:84%
We used to have a saying, what's
good for General Motors is

00:34:30.330 --> 00:34:32.370 align:middle line:90%
good for America.

00:34:32.370 --> 00:34:33.254 align:middle line:90%
That was a time--

00:34:33.254 --> 00:34:33.600 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: That's true.

00:34:33.600 --> 00:34:35.600 align:middle line:84%
>>FITTS: --when there was
a win-win relationship

00:34:35.600 --> 00:34:39.659 align:middle line:84%
between the Dow Jones
and the communities.

00:34:39.659 --> 00:34:42.540 align:middle line:84%
So the question is, how
do we change that back?

00:34:42.540 --> 00:34:46.409 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: In 1989, when you
were the Assistant Secretary

00:34:46.409 --> 00:34:49.230 align:middle line:84%
of Housing and
Urban Development,

00:34:49.230 --> 00:34:51.900 align:middle line:84%
did you foresee the
housing bubble that

00:34:51.900 --> 00:34:55.570 align:middle line:90%
happened 20 years later?

00:34:55.570 --> 00:34:56.409 align:middle line:90%
>>FITTS: No.

00:34:56.409 --> 00:35:01.120 align:middle line:84%
Well, what happened
was I started

00:35:01.120 --> 00:35:03.520 align:middle line:84%
to discover the
extent of the fraud

00:35:03.520 --> 00:35:04.900 align:middle line:90%
when I was Assistant Secretary.

00:35:04.900 --> 00:35:06.317 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: How did
that come to you?

00:35:06.317 --> 00:35:07.275 align:middle line:90%
What did you see first?

00:35:07.275 --> 00:35:09.359 align:middle line:84%
>>FITTS: Well, I'll tell
you one of the first ways

00:35:09.359 --> 00:35:10.290 align:middle line:90%
it came to me.

00:35:10.290 --> 00:35:11.460 align:middle line:90%
I met with the secretary.

00:35:11.460 --> 00:35:13.420 align:middle line:84%
And the secretary said,
I am furious about all

00:35:13.420 --> 00:35:14.220 align:middle line:90%
this corruption.

00:35:14.220 --> 00:35:15.780 align:middle line:84%
I want all this
corruption stopped.

00:35:15.780 --> 00:35:20.010 align:middle line:84%
We just finished both the
Iran-Contra scandal and the S&L

00:35:20.010 --> 00:35:23.910 align:middle line:84%
crisis, so I was there to clean
up and stop the corruption.

00:35:23.910 --> 00:35:26.280 align:middle line:84%
He said, I want all
this corruption stopped.

00:35:26.280 --> 00:35:28.980 align:middle line:84%
And actually, there was a
program called coinsurance,

00:35:28.980 --> 00:35:30.990 align:middle line:90%
a very famous example of this.

00:35:30.990 --> 00:35:33.850 align:middle line:84%
He said, I want this all
stopped and shut down.

00:35:33.850 --> 00:35:36.990 align:middle line:84%
So I said, yes, sir,
left his office.

00:35:36.990 --> 00:35:38.710 align:middle line:90%
And I had a deputy.

00:35:38.710 --> 00:35:40.830 align:middle line:84%
He called the
deputy in and said,

00:35:40.830 --> 00:35:42.540 align:middle line:90%
I just told Fitts to stop this.

00:35:42.540 --> 00:35:43.920 align:middle line:90%
Make sure she fails.

00:35:43.920 --> 00:35:45.090 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Whoa.

00:35:45.090 --> 00:35:45.900 align:middle line:90%
>>FITTS: So we used to have--

00:35:45.900 --> 00:35:46.590 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Mixed signals.

00:35:46.590 --> 00:35:48.840 align:middle line:84%
>>FITTS: [LAUGHS] Well,
because he needed to tell--

00:35:48.840 --> 00:35:49.798 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: He set you up.

00:35:49.798 --> 00:35:52.980 align:middle line:84%
>>FITTS: He needed to tell
the press that he was stopping

00:35:52.980 --> 00:35:56.250 align:middle line:84%
the corruption, but he needed
to keep delivering money

00:35:56.250 --> 00:35:58.860 align:middle line:84%
to the political constituents
in the black budget.

00:35:58.860 --> 00:36:03.900 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: He had no plans to stop
it, did he, from the get go?

00:36:03.900 --> 00:36:06.720 align:middle line:84%
>>FITTS: He didn't
have the power.

00:36:06.720 --> 00:36:11.430 align:middle line:84%
In other words, the Secretary
of HUD does not run HUD.

00:36:11.430 --> 00:36:14.460 align:middle line:84%
HUD is run by the
banks and defense

00:36:14.460 --> 00:36:15.818 align:middle line:90%
contractors who run HUD.

00:36:15.818 --> 00:36:17.110 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Of course, always was.

00:36:17.110 --> 00:36:20.190 align:middle line:84%
>>FITTS: So for example, both
when I was Assistant Secretary

00:36:20.190 --> 00:36:23.130 align:middle line:84%
and then, years later when I
was the lead financial advisor,

00:36:23.130 --> 00:36:25.230 align:middle line:84%
I would ask the defense
contractors for data.

00:36:25.230 --> 00:36:27.030 align:middle line:84%
They would refuse
to give it to me.

00:36:27.030 --> 00:36:28.770 align:middle line:90%
So it was very interesting.

00:36:28.770 --> 00:36:31.140 align:middle line:90%
When I first got to HUD--

00:36:31.140 --> 00:36:33.510 align:middle line:84%
I'm very big on
understanding what

00:36:33.510 --> 00:36:35.970 align:middle line:84%
your scope of
responsibilities are,

00:36:35.970 --> 00:36:39.270 align:middle line:84%
so I read the law
and the regulations

00:36:39.270 --> 00:36:42.840 align:middle line:84%
to know what the Assistant
Secretary of Housing

00:36:42.840 --> 00:36:46.080 align:middle line:84%
federal housing commissioner
is required by law to do.

00:36:46.080 --> 00:36:47.930 align:middle line:84%
So I made a detailed
thing of my scope--

00:36:47.930 --> 00:36:49.740 align:middle line:90%
OK, that's my scope of work.

00:36:49.740 --> 00:36:51.585 align:middle line:84%
And one of my biggest
responsibilities

00:36:51.585 --> 00:36:54.570 align:middle line:84%
was running the
Single-Family Insurance Fund.

00:36:54.570 --> 00:36:57.540 align:middle line:84%
And I was required by law to run
it on a self-supporting basis.

00:36:57.540 --> 00:37:00.378 align:middle line:84%
So the premiums you
charge for the insurance

00:37:00.378 --> 00:37:01.545 align:middle line:90%
have to cover the defaults--

00:37:01.545 --> 00:37:02.700 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: They got
to stand on its own.

00:37:02.700 --> 00:37:04.170 align:middle line:90%
>>FITTS: --and the expenses.

00:37:04.170 --> 00:37:06.233 align:middle line:90%
So I go in.

00:37:06.233 --> 00:37:08.400 align:middle line:84%
And this is very much like
the First American story.

00:37:08.400 --> 00:37:12.450 align:middle line:84%
So I ask my budget officer
for all the budgets.

00:37:12.450 --> 00:37:14.760 align:middle line:84%
It almost could
go to the ceiling,

00:37:14.760 --> 00:37:16.030 align:middle line:90%
the budget justifications.

00:37:16.030 --> 00:37:18.540 align:middle line:84%
I sped read it all weekend
long and called him

00:37:18.540 --> 00:37:20.400 align:middle line:84%
back in on Monday and
said, nowhere here

00:37:20.400 --> 00:37:23.020 align:middle line:84%
does it say if we're
making or losing money.

00:37:23.020 --> 00:37:24.180 align:middle line:90%
Cash in, cash out?

00:37:24.180 --> 00:37:25.110 align:middle line:90%
I can't--

00:37:25.110 --> 00:37:27.093 align:middle line:84%
He said, oh, well,
that's not in the budget.

00:37:27.093 --> 00:37:28.260 align:middle line:90%
I said, well, where is that?

00:37:28.260 --> 00:37:30.228 align:middle line:90%
He said, the accounts have that.

00:37:30.228 --> 00:37:31.770 align:middle line:84%
I said, well, where
are the accounts?

00:37:31.770 --> 00:37:33.937 align:middle line:84%
He said, they report to
another assistant secretary.

00:37:33.937 --> 00:37:36.010 align:middle line:84%
You're not allowed
to talk to them.

00:37:36.010 --> 00:37:37.860 align:middle line:84%
So I always tell
people, George, I

00:37:37.860 --> 00:37:40.380 align:middle line:84%
raised a lot of money for
the president and what I got

00:37:40.380 --> 00:37:43.070 align:middle line:84%
was a pair of cuff links
and the accounts moved over.

00:37:43.070 --> 00:37:47.070 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: So they basically
used you to create this image

00:37:47.070 --> 00:37:49.765 align:middle line:84%
that things are going to change,
things are going to get tough.

00:37:49.765 --> 00:37:52.140 align:middle line:84%
Meanwhile, they never stopped
doing what they were doing.

00:37:52.140 --> 00:37:55.770 align:middle line:84%
>>FITTS: Well, actually, it's
like a pendulum, and it swings.

00:37:55.770 --> 00:37:58.050 align:middle line:84%
You bring in the clean
team, they clean it up.

00:37:58.050 --> 00:38:00.600 align:middle line:84%
Then, you bring the dirty
team in, you harvest it.

00:38:00.600 --> 00:38:02.745 align:middle line:84%
It's like the planters
and the harvesters.

00:38:02.745 --> 00:38:03.090 align:middle line:90%
Do you know what I mean?

00:38:03.090 --> 00:38:05.430 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Did you know that the
dirty team was still out there

00:38:05.430 --> 00:38:06.510 align:middle line:90%
doing what it was doing?

00:38:06.510 --> 00:38:09.780 align:middle line:90%


00:38:09.780 --> 00:38:11.660 align:middle line:84%
>>FITTS: I did not
understand the extent

00:38:11.660 --> 00:38:15.602 align:middle line:90%
to which the finances were run.

00:38:15.602 --> 00:38:17.060 align:middle line:84%
You know, there's
official reality,

00:38:17.060 --> 00:38:18.710 align:middle line:90%
and then there's a reality.

00:38:18.710 --> 00:38:21.590 align:middle line:84%
And by the time I
left, I was certainly

00:38:21.590 --> 00:38:25.280 align:middle line:84%
grappling with the
tension over the gap.

00:38:25.280 --> 00:38:29.653 align:middle line:84%
But I had a hard time
understanding how--

00:38:29.653 --> 00:38:31.070 align:middle line:84%
what I couldn't
figure out is, how

00:38:31.070 --> 00:38:34.040 align:middle line:84%
could they steal that much
money and me not know?

00:38:34.040 --> 00:38:37.820 align:middle line:84%
And it was only after
I started to litigate

00:38:37.820 --> 00:38:41.300 align:middle line:84%
with the Department of
Justice that I had access

00:38:41.300 --> 00:38:44.960 align:middle line:84%
to the people I needed
to be able to estimate

00:38:44.960 --> 00:38:46.550 align:middle line:90%
the covert flows.

00:38:46.550 --> 00:38:49.620 align:middle line:84%
And for me, that was
a mixed blessing.

00:38:49.620 --> 00:38:51.650 align:middle line:84%
It was dangerous,
but it was wonderful,

00:38:51.650 --> 00:38:53.990 align:middle line:84%
because if you're
going to understand

00:38:53.990 --> 00:38:56.090 align:middle line:84%
the global economy or
the American economy,

00:38:56.090 --> 00:38:58.610 align:middle line:84%
you've got to see
the covert flows.

00:38:58.610 --> 00:39:00.770 align:middle line:84%
I'm always telling
people, our world's

00:39:00.770 --> 00:39:02.390 align:middle line:90%
a little bit like Disney World.

00:39:02.390 --> 00:39:04.670 align:middle line:84%
You've got an upstairs world
with Minnie and Mickey.

00:39:04.670 --> 00:39:06.210 align:middle line:84%
And then, you got
a downstairs where

00:39:06.210 --> 00:39:07.880 align:middle line:90%
everything's being engineered.

00:39:07.880 --> 00:39:09.800 align:middle line:84%
And if you're going
to understand,

00:39:09.800 --> 00:39:11.980 align:middle line:84%
you have to understand
both together.

00:39:11.980 --> 00:39:13.530 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Is everything
rampant now?

00:39:13.530 --> 00:39:16.680 align:middle line:90%
Is it just out of control?

00:39:16.680 --> 00:39:18.620 align:middle line:84%
>>FITTS: Well, I would
say that what we've had

00:39:18.620 --> 00:39:22.440 align:middle line:84%
is a huge debasement
of the culture that

00:39:22.440 --> 00:39:25.332 align:middle line:90%
has made it much harder.

00:39:25.332 --> 00:39:26.790 align:middle line:84%
If you're a financial
professional,

00:39:26.790 --> 00:39:29.580 align:middle line:84%
if you're in bank,
if you're insurance,

00:39:29.580 --> 00:39:33.858 align:middle line:84%
if you're in brokerage, it's
much harder to do your work.

00:39:33.858 --> 00:39:36.150 align:middle line:84%
One-- because there's so much
more fraud in the system.

00:39:36.150 --> 00:39:41.280 align:middle line:90%


00:39:41.280 --> 00:39:44.550 align:middle line:84%
Finding people of integrity
is a bigger challenge,

00:39:44.550 --> 00:39:46.608 align:middle line:84%
finding institutions
of integrity.

00:39:46.608 --> 00:39:48.150 align:middle line:84%
And you'll see
institutions too, now,

00:39:48.150 --> 00:39:50.940 align:middle line:84%
that I would have
thought was unthinkable.

00:39:50.940 --> 00:39:53.250 align:middle line:84%
So I'm always telling my
clients and subscribers,

00:39:53.250 --> 00:39:59.810 align:middle line:84%
you can't depend on the Federal
Credit to bail everything out.

00:39:59.810 --> 00:40:02.420 align:middle line:84%
In all these different areas
of your financial life,

00:40:02.420 --> 00:40:05.147 align:middle line:84%
you've got to find people in
companies with real integrity.

00:40:05.147 --> 00:40:07.730 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: What do you think they
use this money for, Catherine?

00:40:07.730 --> 00:40:09.305 align:middle line:90%
The $21 trillion-- where is it?

00:40:09.305 --> 00:40:11.180 align:middle line:84%
>>FITTS: Well, this is
how I met you, George.

00:40:11.180 --> 00:40:12.860 align:middle line:84%
[LAUGHING] I don't
know if you remember.

00:40:12.860 --> 00:40:15.660 align:middle line:84%
I did my first interview
with you in 2005.

00:40:15.660 --> 00:40:17.140 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Yeah, I remember that.

00:40:17.140 --> 00:40:18.723 align:middle line:84%
>>FITTS: And you
said, don't you think

00:40:18.723 --> 00:40:22.790 align:middle line:84%
they're using it to deal
with whatever is going on

00:40:22.790 --> 00:40:24.050 align:middle line:90%
with the UFO phenomenon?

00:40:24.050 --> 00:40:26.092 align:middle line:84%
I said no, George, I think
they're just stealing.

00:40:26.092 --> 00:40:28.830 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHS] And I think it's both.

00:40:28.830 --> 00:40:31.730 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Are they lining
their own personal pockets?

00:40:31.730 --> 00:40:35.900 align:middle line:84%
>>FITTS: So we're talking about
far too much money to be just

00:40:35.900 --> 00:40:39.710 align:middle line:84%
a group of guys on Wall Street
with Ferraris and off-shore--

00:40:39.710 --> 00:40:41.390 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: And nice houses, yeah.

00:40:41.390 --> 00:40:42.830 align:middle line:84%
>>FITTS: So I'm not
saying that people haven't

00:40:42.830 --> 00:40:43.820 align:middle line:90%
made an awful lot of money.

00:40:43.820 --> 00:40:44.660 align:middle line:90%
They have.

00:40:44.660 --> 00:40:47.310 align:middle line:84%
So you've had kind
of a gold rush.

00:40:47.310 --> 00:40:50.240 align:middle line:84%
And what you've done
is you've used money

00:40:50.240 --> 00:40:51.950 align:middle line:90%
to incentivize people.

00:40:51.950 --> 00:40:54.140 align:middle line:84%
I mean, what's
amazing to me is--

00:40:54.140 --> 00:40:55.640 align:middle line:84%
if you throw enough
money at people,

00:40:55.640 --> 00:40:58.070 align:middle line:84%
it's amazing what you
can get them to do.

00:40:58.070 --> 00:41:01.400 align:middle line:84%
So there's no doubt
that making people rich

00:41:01.400 --> 00:41:06.010 align:middle line:84%
has been very helpful in
getting them to destroy--

00:41:06.010 --> 00:41:08.390 align:middle line:84%
if you look at the
freedoms that we enjoy here

00:41:08.390 --> 00:41:11.480 align:middle line:84%
versus other places in the
world, it's extraordinary.

00:41:11.480 --> 00:41:12.345 align:middle line:90%
It's wonderful.

00:41:12.345 --> 00:41:13.970 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Of course,
it feels wonderful.

00:41:13.970 --> 00:41:15.410 align:middle line:90%
>>FITTS: Yeah and it's hard.

00:41:15.410 --> 00:41:16.770 align:middle line:90%
I'll give you a perfect example.

00:41:16.770 --> 00:41:20.130 align:middle line:84%
I wrote a great article
called, "William Diefenderfer,

00:41:20.130 --> 00:41:21.380 align:middle line:90%
The Hit Man of Student Loans."

00:41:21.380 --> 00:41:24.680 align:middle line:84%
I had a former partner
who was very instrumental,

00:41:24.680 --> 00:41:29.570 align:middle line:84%
I believe, in engineering
the destruction of consumer

00:41:29.570 --> 00:41:32.060 align:middle line:84%
protections for student
loans so that kids

00:41:32.060 --> 00:41:34.340 align:middle line:90%
can't declare bankruptcy now.

00:41:34.340 --> 00:41:37.270 align:middle line:90%


00:41:37.270 --> 00:41:39.740 align:middle line:84%
And in the article,
I talk about how hard

00:41:39.740 --> 00:41:42.230 align:middle line:84%
it is for me to
believe that someone

00:41:42.230 --> 00:41:46.010 align:middle line:84%
who was such a high quality
person that I would want him

00:41:46.010 --> 00:41:48.310 align:middle line:90%
on my board would do something.

00:41:48.310 --> 00:41:49.400 align:middle line:90%
Why?

00:41:49.400 --> 00:41:50.900 align:middle line:90%
I mean, here's someone who--

00:41:50.900 --> 00:41:52.730 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: It's beyond anything.

00:41:52.730 --> 00:41:55.100 align:middle line:84%
>>FITTS: The United States
has been so wonderful

00:41:55.100 --> 00:41:58.250 align:middle line:84%
that he has been
so blessed in terms

00:41:58.250 --> 00:42:00.800 align:middle line:84%
of professional accomplishments
and making money.

00:42:00.800 --> 00:42:03.650 align:middle line:84%
Why would you turn around and
destroy the next generation?

00:42:03.650 --> 00:42:04.790 align:middle line:90%
Why would you do that?

00:42:04.790 --> 00:42:08.050 align:middle line:90%
Because it's an entrapment.

00:42:08.050 --> 00:42:10.610 align:middle line:84%
And it's shocking to me that
someone I know and cared about

00:42:10.610 --> 00:42:11.537 align:middle line:90%
would do that.

00:42:11.537 --> 00:42:13.370 align:middle line:84%
And that was the problem
I had in Washington

00:42:13.370 --> 00:42:16.970 align:middle line:84%
with what we were doing in
the poorer neighborhoods.

00:42:16.970 --> 00:42:19.220 align:middle line:84%
Because what we were
doing was lawless,

00:42:19.220 --> 00:42:21.410 align:middle line:84%
and it was shocking
to me that people

00:42:21.410 --> 00:42:23.030 align:middle line:90%
would go along with that.

00:42:23.030 --> 00:42:29.150 align:middle line:84%
So I just think, when you
have this much secret money,

00:42:29.150 --> 00:42:30.890 align:middle line:84%
the problem with
secret money, George,

00:42:30.890 --> 00:42:34.520 align:middle line:84%
is it's impossible to
optimize it and use it well.

00:42:34.520 --> 00:42:36.410 align:middle line:90%
It goes out of control.

00:42:36.410 --> 00:42:39.180 align:middle line:84%
So there's something happening
that's out of control.

00:42:39.180 --> 00:42:41.180 align:middle line:84%
And the question is, what
are they dealing with?

00:42:41.180 --> 00:42:45.320 align:middle line:84%
I think a lot of it is going
into secret military expenses.

00:42:45.320 --> 00:42:47.830 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Absolutely--
space programs.

00:42:47.830 --> 00:42:49.970 align:middle line:84%
>>FITTS: A lot of it's
going into space programs.

00:42:49.970 --> 00:42:52.040 align:middle line:84%
I don't know if you saw
this, but at the D-Day--

00:42:52.040 --> 00:42:52.915 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Festivities.

00:42:52.915 --> 00:42:56.090 align:middle line:84%
>>FITTS: --the president
made a reference to,

00:42:56.090 --> 00:42:58.173 align:middle line:84%
we got a man on the moon,
and then we went beyond.

00:42:58.173 --> 00:42:58.973 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHS]

00:42:58.973 --> 00:43:00.053 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Yeah, oops.

00:43:00.053 --> 00:43:01.970 align:middle line:84%
>>FITTS: Then he tweets
out that he wants NASA

00:43:01.970 --> 00:43:04.460 align:middle line:90%
to focus on getting to Mars.

00:43:04.460 --> 00:43:06.462 align:middle line:84%
You know, it's really
funny, because he

00:43:06.462 --> 00:43:07.670 align:middle line:90%
doesn't like keeping secrets.

00:43:07.670 --> 00:43:09.890 align:middle line:90%
He wants to share something.

00:43:09.890 --> 00:43:13.710 align:middle line:84%
So I think a lot of the money
is has gone into space programs.

00:43:13.710 --> 00:43:16.568 align:middle line:84%
If you look at the
percentage of the GNP

00:43:16.568 --> 00:43:18.110 align:middle line:84%
and the federal
budget that was going

00:43:18.110 --> 00:43:22.460 align:middle line:84%
into space at the end of
the Kennedy administration

00:43:22.460 --> 00:43:25.485 align:middle line:84%
and the end of the Johnson
administration, it's gone down.

00:43:25.485 --> 00:43:27.110 align:middle line:84%
And I think it's
because of the secret.

00:43:27.110 --> 00:43:28.777 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: The secret
went up, absolutely.

00:43:28.777 --> 00:43:30.950 align:middle line:84%
>>FITTS: Right, so I think
the trajectory continued,

00:43:30.950 --> 00:43:32.960 align:middle line:84%
but the gap between
what's public

00:43:32.960 --> 00:43:35.930 align:middle line:84%
and that trajectory
has been part of this.

00:43:35.930 --> 00:43:39.753 align:middle line:84%
To do that, you've needed
a vast underground.

00:43:39.753 --> 00:43:40.670 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Network, yep.

00:43:40.670 --> 00:43:42.170 align:middle line:84%
>>FITTS: So I've
tried to understand

00:43:42.170 --> 00:43:43.610 align:middle line:84%
what the underground
installations

00:43:43.610 --> 00:43:44.943 align:middle line:90%
and transportation networks are.

